ust-lang/rust/labels/regression-from-stable-to-beta", "name": "regression-from-stable-to-beta", "color": "e4008a", "default": false, "description": "Performance or correctness regression from stable to beta."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 14, "created_at": "2017-12-22T03:23:38Z", "updated_at": "2018-01-12T23:28:18Z", "closed_at": "2018-01-12T23:28:18Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Beginning with `rustc 1.24.0-nightly (250b49205 2017-12-21)`, `rustc` fails to find the appropriate file for a module when the module root is not `mod_name/mod.rs` or `mod_name.rs` (i.e, when using `#[path]`). This has broken `ring`, which has the following `mod` declarations:\r\n\r\nIn `lib.rs`:\r\n```rust\r\n#[path = \"arithmetic/arithmetic.rs\"]\r\nmod arithmetic;\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn `arithmetic/arithmetic.rs`:\r\n```rust\r\npub mod montgomery;\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd `arithmetic/montgomery.rs` contains the `montgomery` module code. This results in the following error:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nerror[E0583]: file not found for module `montgomery`\r\n  --> $home/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/ring-0.12.1/src/arithmetic/arithmetic.rs:15:9\r\n   |\r\n15 | pub mod montgomery;\r\n   |         ^^^^^^^^^^\r\n   |\r\n   = help: name the file either arithmetic/montgomery.rs or arithmetic/montgomery/mod.rs inside the directory \"$home/.cargo/registry/src/github.com-1ecc6299db9ec823/ring-0.12.1/src/arithmetic\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRelated issues: https://github.com/briansmith/ring/issues/598, https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/46531", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github